premise_source_doc_sentence: The Dunkirk evacuation , code-named Operation Dynamo , also known as the Miracle of Dunkirk , was the evacuation of Allied soldiers from the beaches and harbour of Dunkirk , France , between 26 May and 4 June 1940 , during World War II .

The 1940 Dunkirk Veterans ' Association was an association of British service veterans `` who served at Dunkirk and other ports of evacuation between 10 May and June 1940 '' - that is in the Dunkirk evacuation of 1940 , including those who were taken prisoner .
The Dunkirk evacuation -- a major military operation that took place during the 1940 Battle of Dunkirk .
The army was to halt for three days , which gave the Allies sufficient time to organise the Dunkirk evacuation and build a defensive line .
During World War II , the port closed to civilian boat usage and 44,000 personnel used the port during the Dunkirk Evacuation .
